Pedal-focused performance: the musical performance is focused on transforming a pre-recorded sound-source using effect pedals. This gesture is a reversal of the traditional use of effect pedals: they are not supposed to be the center of the performance. Rather, they usually embellish the sound of a guitar or a synth. The musical gestures then focus on the guitar/synth, and the pedals are left relatively untouched. Effect pedals are amongst the most "traditional" noise instruments, often stacked one after another, connected to a contact microphone or set up in a "no-input" loop (where the output of a mixer is run through pedals&nbsp; which are plugged in the same mixer, causing feedback that is modulated by the pedals).
